    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Start Merry and Boromir.  Get Aragorn as soon as I can.  With his signet he can keep all the fighters healthy.  Use the Stealth cards to dodge fights or pump the Hobbits later on.  Dagger Strike works with both races.  Athelas for condition removal and extra healing.  The twilight denial cards help at the larger site numbers to keep that extra minion off the table.  Rotate Aragorn and Boromir on the larger minions so the wounds are spread out, throw Merry in as well because with 4 vitality he can take a good hiding.<br>
<br>
Moria swarms the Fellowship, lots of minions plus a few bigger ones thrown in.  Host of Thousands and They Are Coming to keep those cards moving and bring up the right ones.  Goblin Armory to go in when I get a few but the Wallcrawlers and Archer help a bit with non-directed archery. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
